    "title": "Mid-Level Plant Manager at NTPC",
    "description": "NTPC is actively seeking a talented and motivated Plant Manager to join our dynamic team in Nagpur. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout NTPC:\nNTPC is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Referral bonus program\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Nagpur, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with NTPC!",
